Clinical Diagnosis : LUNG CA
Gross Description : A. Received fresh at the frozen desk is a specimen labeled " left upper lobe " .
It consists of a 357 gram lobectomy specimen of the left upper lobe measuring 24.0 x 9.5 x 3.5 cm .
The bronchial remnant is approximately 0.3 cm in length .
In the central segment .
there is a poorly circumscribed firm gray ? white tumor measuring 4.2 x 3.5 x 3.0 cm with scattered necrosis and hemorrhage that is 2.5 cm from bronchial margin .
The tumor causes retraction of the overlying pleura , but does not grossly invade through the pleura , which has a smooth , glistening surface .
The tumor grossly invades an adjacent bronchus .
The tumor grossly surrounds large vessels .
The remainder of the lung is unremarkable .
There are four anthracotic hilar lymph nodes , the largest measuring 1.2 cm in greatest dimension .
